  "title": "QA Assistant Manager [WCNH]",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Oversee the overall quality and safety of food products at the Central Kitchen.</li>\n  <li>Ensure food products comply with company standards and regulatory requirements.</li>\n  <li>Develop, review, and update quality and safety policies and procedures.</li>\n  <li>Conduct regular inspections and audits to maintain high quality standards.</li>\n  <li>Maintain and continuously improve existing quality control procedures.</li>\n  <li>Investigate and address customer feedback regarding product quality.</li>\n  <li>Verify that all products are produced in compliance with established QA protocols.</li>\n  <li>Ensure adherence to standard operating procedures (SOPs) across all operations.</li>\n  <li>Monitor and maintain product quality standards consistently.</li>\n  <li>Ensure all activities comply with HACCP and AVA/NEA guidelines.</li>\n  <li>Supervise and manage all quality assurance activities within the team.</li>\n  <li>Support product and process development, including R&amp;D, food tasting, and process improvements.</li>\n  <li>Assist in research and development initiatives for new products and processes.</li>\n  <li>Perform any other tasks assigned by the Chief Quality Assurance Officer or Manage</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
